{
  "texts": [
    "A restricted body of literature has introduced and examined a collection of domain-agnostic evaluation metrics, which amalgamate intrinsic and extrinsic measurements for LLMs in the healthcare domain.",
    "Notably, Laing et al.",
    "5 have presented a multi-metric approach, as part of the HELM benchmark, to scrutinize LLMs concerning their accuracy, calibration (proficiency in assigning meaningful probabilities for generated text), robustness, fairness, bias, toxicity, and efficiency.",
    "Likewise, Wang et al.",
    "6 have assessed the trustworthiness of GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 from eight discerning aspects encompassing toxicity, bias, robustness, privacy, machine ethics, and fairness."
  ]
}